# joining df's
loans <- loans %>% 
  rename(state_abb = addr_state) %>% 
  left_join(states_info, by = "state_abb") %>% 
  left_join(grades, by = "sub_grade", .after = sub_grade) %>% 
  clean_names()

  count(issue_d)

loans_trim %>%

loans_trim

# types of p2p loans over time
loans_trim %>% 
  group_by(purpose, issue_d) %>% 
  summarise(count = n()) %>% 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = issue_d, y = count, colour = purpose) +
  geom_line() 
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'purpose'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
